        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10697",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rob",
                        "name": "rob",
                        "displayName": "Rob Allen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Isn't it just easier to cast after the retrieval for the few times you need to worry about it?\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rob",
                        "name": "rob",
                        "displayName": "Rob Allen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-08-12T15:21:51.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-08-12T15:21:51.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10698",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=andries",
                        "name": "andries",
                        "displayName": "Andries Seutens",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Agreed. Casting is the way to go here...",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=andries",
                        "name": "andries",
                        "displayName": "Andries Seutens",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-08-14T04:25:34.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-08-14T04:25:34.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10707",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=sekundek",
                        "name": "sekundek",
                        "displayName": "Uros",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "What about default value? Many app have option to just override what you need.\n\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=sekundek",
                        "name": "sekundek",
                        "displayName": "Uros",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-08-16T04:28:46.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-08-16T04:28:46.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10708",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rob",
                        "name": "rob",
                        "displayName": "Rob Allen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "There is certainly an argument for a getWithDefault() type function. That's not this Issue though.\n\nI've added it to the Zend_Config enhancements wiki page (http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/wiki\/display\/ZFDEV\/Zend_Config) but I can't think of a good interface at the moment.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rob",
                        "name": "rob",
                        "displayName": "Rob Allen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-08-16T04:34:55.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-08-16T04:34:55.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10709",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=sekundek",
                        "name": "sekundek",
                        "displayName": "Uros",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "With default values I add this get*** methods and while I was writing this I add those helper functions. \n\nI know this is maybe two different things here. But casting every thime I get some data from config. I know it's cleaner way to use jutst\n(string)$config->some->config. But I use config from Java and I thought that Zend_Config could use such helper functions.\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=sekundek",
                        "name": "sekundek",
                        "displayName": "Uros",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-08-16T05:26:46.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-08-16T05:26:46.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10710",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rob",
                        "name": "rob",
                        "displayName": "Rob Allen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The thing is, you rarely need to cast in PHP: it'll sort out the type appropriately for the situation.\n\ne.g.\n\nconfig.ini:\n    [general]\n    debug = 1\n\n\n$config = new Zend_Config(new Zend_Config_Ini('config.ini', 'general'));\n\n$debug = $config->debug;\n\nif($debug == true)\n{\n   \/\/ we end up in here as string of \"1\" is converted to true by PHP\n}\n\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rob",
                        "name": "rob",
                        "displayName": "Rob Allen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-08-16T05:32:13.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-08-16T05:32:13.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10716",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=sekundek",
                        "name": "sekundek",
                        "displayName": "Uros",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "What about just get function?\n\n public function get($name,$default=null)\n\nHere you can use defaults.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=sekundek",
                        "name": "sekundek",
                        "displayName": "Uros",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-08-17T01:21:38.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-08-17T01:21:38.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
    },
